Instructions Step 1: Boot your computer. During POST, BIOS information is displayed on the screen for a short period of time. Do not log on to Windows. Question: What key or combination of keys is used to run Setup on your computer? --BIOS Setup Key: F2

Step 2: Restart your computer and enter Setup. The BIOS Setup Utility or UEFI screen appears. Questions: Who is the manufacturer of the BIOS? Which BIOS version is installed in your computer?

--BIOS Manufacturer: American Megatrends International, LLC. --Installed BIOS Version: FB03 (16/05/2025) --BIOS Mode: UEFI --System Manufacturer: GIGABYTE --System Model: GIGABYTE GAMING A16 CTH

Step 3: Search the Internet to find the most current version of BIOS for the motherboard. Caution: Do not update your BIOS at this time. Questions: What is the current BIOS version available for the motherboard? --FB04 (December 9, 2025)

What features, if any, have been added to the new BIOS version? --The new BIOS version includes BIOS FB04 and EC F004, which improves system stability and hardware compatibility.

What changes, if any, have been made to the new BIOS version to fix problems? --The BIOS update fixes potential system issues and improves overall system reliability and performance.

What are the instructions to update the new BIOS version? --Download the BIOS update from the GIGABYTE support website, connect the laptop to AC power, run the BIOS update utility, and follow the on-screen instructions. Do not power off the system during the update process.
